Information
------------------------------

Penelope Keith's Hidden Villages: 2014
Cream teas, bunting, thatched cottages swathed in roses. For generations this rural idyll of the village has conjured the very best of Britain. 
Penelope Keith explores our relationship with the village, discovering traditions under threat and communities undergoing huge changes, as she looks at what the future holds for rural communities.


1)  East Anglia 
Penelope attends a traditional village regatta on the Norfolk Broads, takes to the air over the village of Little Snoring, and witnesses the formation wheelbarrow display by the Red Sparrows!

2)  North Wales 
Penelope explores the rugged hills and valleys of north Wales, goes to her first music festival, meets the Cheshire set and attends an ancient fertility festival in Staffordshire

3)  Wessex 
Penelope follows her guidebook through Dorset, Somerset and Wiltshire, including a visit to Castle Combe, voted Britain's prettiest village
